place.name: RHOSCROWDDER
place.gazetteerText: RHOSCROWTHER, a parish in the district and county of Pembroke; on Milford haven, 2 miles by water S of Milford r. station. Post-town, Pembroke. Acres, 2, 536; of which 170 are water. Real property, £2, 563. Pop., 202. Houses, 39. The property is divided among a few. The living is a rectory in the diocese of St. Davids. Value, £307.* Patron, the Lord Chancellor. The church is old but good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
